    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "~Have you considered using the [connector](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/connectors/connectInfiniteHits.html)? By using a connector you have a complete control over the rendering.~\r\n\r\nMy bad. The only problem I see here is that the allItems template gets a result object, and the infinite hits gives an aggregation of all the hits. Maybe there's something wrong here and the allItems should get a result object but a list of hits... That would be a breaking change.\r\n\r\nI'm wondering if we really need the whole result object for `allItems` anyway?",
